text: Anastasiya Kirpichnikova (born 24 June 2000) is a Russian swimmer. In 2019, she represented Russia at the 2019 World Aquatics Championships held in Gwangju, South Korea. She competed in the women's 800 metre freestyle and women's 1500 metre freestyle events.
